==English==

===Etymology===
From the Latin word ''vicenārius'', meaning "of the number twenty", from ''vigintī'', meaning "twenty"

===Adjective===
'''vicenarian''' (''non-comparable'')

# Between the ages of 20 and 29, inclusive. In one's third [[decade]].

===Noun===
'''vicenarian''' (''plural'' '''[[vicenarians]]''')

# A person whose [[age]] is between [[twenty]] and [[twenty-nine]] years, inclusive; someone in his or her [[twenties]]. Someone in his or her third [[decade]].

